- Install `django-redis` using pip: `pip install django-redis`
- Update Django settings to use Redis as session backend:
  ```python
  SESSION_ENGINE = "django.contrib.sessions.backends.cache"
  CACHES = {
      "default": {
          "BACKEND": "django_redis.cache.RedisCache",
          "LOCATION": "redis://127.0.0.1:6379/1",
          "OPTIONS": {
              "CLIENT_CLASS": "django_redis.client.DefaultClient",
          }
      }
  }
  ```
- Ensure Redis server is running on `localhost` at port `6379`.
- Use the latest version of Django and `django-redis` for optimal performance.
- Configure `SESSION_COOKIE_AGE` in settings to control session expiration time.
